\begin_layout Standard
In all three figures, the 4 curves given by zero order interpolation don't
 divers a lot compared with the linear interpolation one.
 The result of MDFT also shows that zero order interpolation gives large
 energy error with a DCF of 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{\max}=1$
\end_inset

, and has convergency problems in certain cases.
 As a conclusion, the linear interpolation scheme is absolutely needed.
 On the other hand, as seen in eq.
 (
